

get_rpc_createerr(3rpc)                   get_rpc_createerr(3rpc)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] file -lnsl #include <rpc/rpc.h>

       rpc_createerr_t get_rpc_createerr(void);

       int set_rpc_createerr(rpc_createerr_t);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  get_rpc_createerr and set_rpc_createerr functions are
       used in rpc applications to set and return  the  value  in
       rpc_createerr.   rpc_createerr  is  defined as a structure
       that  contains  the  following  members:  enum   clnt_stat
       cf_stat;  struct  rpc_err  cf_error;  These  functions are
       required by applications compiled with the -Kthread option
       if  the  user  needs to set the thread-specific version of
       rpc_createerr.

FFiilleess
       Network Services Library (shared object)

UUssaaggee
       While get_rpc_createerr and set_rpc_createerr are designed
       for use in multi-threaded applications, they are available
       for use in non-reentrant code and may be incorporated if a
       need is anticipated to convert to reentrant code later on.

